From: Wayen Yan <win847@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] thermal: airoha: Fix sensor interval FIELD_PREP mask

The second field targets FILT_INTERVAL again, leaving SEN_INTERVAL at zero.
Use the sensor interval mask for the documented 379-cycle value.

Signed-off-by: Wayen Yan <win847@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
+++ b/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
@@ -503,7 +503,7 @@ static void airoha_thermal_setup_monitor
 	 */
 	regmap_write(priv->map, EN7581_TEMPMONCTL2,
 		     FIELD_PREP(EN7581_FILT_INTERVAL, 1) |
-		     FIELD_PREP(EN7581_FILT_INTERVAL, 379));
+		     FIELD_PREP(EN7581_SEN_INTERVAL, 379));
 
 	/* AHB poll is set to 146 * 68.64 = 10.02us */
 	regmap_write(priv->map, EN7581_TEMPAHBPOLL,
